<div style="overflow: hidden;" id="wpbody-content" aria-label="Main content" tabindex="0">
    <div class="wrap">
        <h2> Help</h2>
        <table style="width:70%" class="wp-list-table widefat  striped items">
        	<thead><th colspan="4"><div align="center"><h3>How to Display Ads on Frontend?</h3></div></th></thead>
            <thead><th style="width: 10%"><b>No</b></th><th style="width: 25%"><b>Title</b></th><th style="width: 40%"><b>Discription</b></th><th style="width: 35%"><b>Code</b></th></thead>
	        <tbody >
            <tr style="background-color: #f2f2f2 !important;"><td >1</td><td>Page Editor</td><td><p>Go to any Page or Post and then Add Short code into Editor Section then will see Ads into Front End Content Section.We can Add Short code between the content if we need ads between 2 Paragraphs.</p></td> <td>"[Customads id=123456]"</td></tr>
	        <tr><td>2</td><td>Text Widget</td><td><p>Go to Widget Section and Add Short code into Wordpress Text Widget which will show added ads on Front End into that Sidebar.We can Provide Widget Title and We can add Text Content into Text Widget with Ads Short Code.</p></td> <td>"[Customads id=123456]"</td> </tr>
	        <tr style="background-color: #f2f2f2 !important;"><td>3</td><td>Custom Ads Widget</td><td><p> Select Appearance->Widget, Select customads widget and drop it to any widget appearance area, put title for an ads select any ads from dropdown and select checkbox to Display Customads Title, Display Customads Description and it will be Displayed on frontend before Ads.</p></td><td>"[Customads id=123456]"</td></tr>
	        <tr><td>4</td><td>PHP Code</td><td><p>Admin can Add Custom Short code into any Theme Page Via Editor or Opening Php file. Admin will place Short code and then ads will be displayed on front end on that section.</p></td> <td>do_shortcode "[Customads id=123456]" </td></tr>
            </tbody>
    	</table>
    </div> 
</div>   